===References===
*[[Strong's concordance]] number:  [http://www.biblestudytools.net/Lexicons/Greek/grk.cgi?number=165&version=kjv G165] 

===Pronunciation===
*αἰών / aiōn / ahee-ohn'
=== Etymology ===

*From the same as [[ἀεί]] {{GG|104}}; properly an age; by extension perpetuity (also past); by implication the world; specifically (Jewish) a Messianic period (present or future):  
=== Noun ===
[[age]], [[course]], [[eternal]], (for) [[ever]] (-more), [n-]ever, (beginning of the, while the) world (began, without end). 

=== Compare ===
[[χρόνος]] {{GG|5550}}.